# Visual-only transitions (scope lock)

Read `footiebitz/docs/TRANSITIONS-SCOPE.md` before changing preview, export, or timeline transition behavior.

## Frozen systems

Do **not** modify behavior of: voiceover generation, voice speed, `voiceoverDurationMs`, scene `durationMs`/`startMs`/`endMs`, subtitle chunk timing, subtitle effects, caption mode, generated captions, export audio mux, or scene image fit/fill/position.

## Rules

1. Transitions are **visual overlays only** — use `transition.effect` and `transition.durationMs`.
2. **Never** add transition duration to total playback length.
3. Overlay within existing scene time (prefer tail of outgoing scene or head of incoming scene).
4. **Never** render `TRANSITION_CARD_TITLE` or fake transition scenes in preview/export video.
5. Scene/subtitle/voiceover sync stays on `getSceneTimingAtGlobalTime` — transitions are a render layer, not a second timeline.
6. Export: keep scene-only render path until overlay compositing is implemented; do not enable `renderTransitions` without scope QA passing.

## Before merging transition work

Run: `npm run test:transitions-scope`, `npm run test:voice-speed-qa`, `npm run test:timing-subtitle-qa`, `npm run lint`, `npm run build`.
